                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2981</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs at
                            Nanking</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chinese Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="94" xml:id="d516fn94">Copy of telegram handed by the First Secretary of
                        the Chinese Legation to Mr. Hansford S. Miller of the Division of Far
                        Eastern Affairs on November 25, 1931.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-24">November 24,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Lately Japanese have been intensely circulating news that the Chinese troops at
                    Chinchow will attack the Japanese troops and Chang Hsueh-Liang will declare war.
                    Japan’s intention is to launch immediate attack upon Chinchow. According to
                    railway reports Japanese gunboat <hi rend="italic">Kuoa</hi> arrived 23rd
                    declaring to protect wireless station but evidently to help attack Chinchow.</p>
            </div>
